meanings.definition: To move faster than someone or something else.
meanings.sent1: The cheetah outspeeded the gazelle in the race.
meanings.sent2: The car outspeeded the bicycle on the highway.
meanings.sent3: The tortoise tried to outspeeded the hare in the friendly competition.
meanings.sent4: The wind outspeeded the runner, pushing him forward effortlessly.
meanings.sent5: The rocket outspeeded all other vehicles, soaring into the sky at incredible speed.

meanings.sent1: She outspeeded her previous record in the sprint.
meanings.sent2: The champion outspeeded all opponents in the final lap.
meanings.sent3: The snail outspeeded the turtle in the slowest race ever.
meanings.sent4: Time outspeeded him, leaving him behind in the past.
meanings.sent5: The river outspeeded its banks, flooding the nearby fields.
